article.description: Devon Peltier scored 24 points and Perry Webster hit the go-ahead 3-pointer to give Cal State Fullerton a 62-59 win on Sunday.
article.headline: Cal State Fullerton holds on against San Diego
article.linkText: Cal SCal State Fullerton holds on against San Diego
article.story: SAN DIEGO -- Devon Peltier scored 24 points and Perry Webster hit the go-ahead 3-pointer to give Cal State Fullerton a 62-59 win on Sunday. Cal State Fullerton (1-3) held the lead for virtually the entire game until the Toreros hit four 3-pointers in a 3-minute stretch to go ahead 58-55 with 3:21 left. But Webster hit two free throws and sank a 3-point shot with 1:56 remaining to put the Titans ahead for good at 60-58. San Diego (1-3) had plenty of chances down the stretch. But the Toreros missed three of four free-throw tries in the final 1:39. They also missed three shots in the final 10 seconds before Peltier grabbed a rebound, was fouled and made both free throws. Matt Dorr then missed a 3-pointer from about 23 feet at the buzzer that would have tied it. Devin Ginty led San Diego with 17 points and Dorr added 12.
